      "notes": "1. Event Objective \nThe meeting focused on Ignite, an internship fair designed for 3rd-year and \ngraduating students. The event aims to bridge the gap between students and the \nprofessional world. \nVenue: Main Library (Pending administrative approval).&nbsp;<div>&nbsp;2. Operational Tasks &amp; Outreach \n● Company list: \n○ The team will filter the existing list in the telegram from last \nyear to keep high-value companies. \n \n \n○ Maissa (Relex &amp; communication) will add new contacts from \nRecruitment Day and lead the initial organization. \n● Startup Engagement: \n○ Emphasis on bringing more startups to the event.&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;3. Logistics &amp; Administration \n● Administrative Liaison: Leena (SG) is responsible for meeting with \nDerbal to finalize the paperwork required for the library \nreservation. \n● The Incubator Strategy (in case we don't find a sponsor for \nStudups): To attract startups without a large cash budget, we will \noffer certificates and potential spots in the incubator. \n○ Action: We need a volunteer with a good relationship with Dr. \nBrahimi to negotiate this.&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;4. Financial Strategy \nThe administration has set a strict limit of 30 million for one single \nproject. Since they rejected separate budgets for the podcast or Studups, \nthe team will consolidate efforts under the Ignite umbrella. \n● Food &amp; Catering: Currently allocated to Fickratech via the school \nbudget. \n● Sponsorship Opportunities: * Yani is tracking a lead on a company \nto sponsor Fickratech costs. \n \n● Club Collaboration: To maximize the 30M budget, the team suggests \ncollaborating with another club on a \"shared project\" to pool \nresources and benefits.&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;Immediate Action Plan&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;Leena: Secure reservation papers from Derbal for the \nLibrary.&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;Maisa: Complete the filtered company list (Telegram + \nRecruitment Day).&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;TBD: Meet with Dr. Brahimi regarding the incubator \nincentive.&nbsp;</div><div>Team: Identify a partner club for budget/project \ncollaboration.</div>",
